# {{.Name}}

A Connect RPC service project built with [Forge](https://github.com/reliant-labs/forge).

## Quick Start

### 1. Install dependencies
```bash
task deps
```

### 2. Add a service
```bash
forge add service myservice
```

### 3. Define your proto
Edit the generated proto file in `proto/services/myservice/v1/myservice.proto`:
```protobuf
syntax = "proto3";

package myservice.v1;

option go_package = "{{.Module}}/gen/myservice/v1;myservicev1";

service MyService {
  rpc SayHello(HelloRequest) returns (HelloResponse);
}

message HelloRequest {
  string name = 1;
}

message HelloResponse {
  string message = 1;
}
```

### 4. Generate code from protos
```bash
forge generate
```

### 5. Build and run
```bash
task build
task dev
```

## CLI Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `forge new` | Create a new project |
| `forge add service <name>` | Add a Go service |
| `forge add frontend <name>` | Add a Next.js frontend app |
| `forge generate` | Generate code from proto files |
| `forge lint` | Lint proto and Go code |
| `forge build` | Build the project |
| `forge run` | Run the dev environment |
| `forge deploy <env>` | Deploy to an environment |
| `forge test` | Run tests |
| `forge db` | Database commands |

## Task Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `task proto` | Generate protobuf code via buf |
| `task build` | Build service binaries |
| `task test` | Run tests with coverage |
| `task lint` | Run linters |
| `task dev` | Start services with Air hot-reload |
| `task dev-up` | Create k3d cluster, build, and deploy |
| `task dev-down` | Delete k3d development cluster |
| `task clean` | Clean generated files and build artifacts |

